snippet.title: October Book Haul Part One | 2020
snippet.description:
I don’t feel like I have done a haul in forever so this could actually be a mix of late September and the first of October’s book hauls... but does it really matter? Either way it is a biggun (oo-er) as I have over thirty books to chat through with you. You may need a cuppa and a sit down with this #BookHaul today, ha. Hope you enjoy.

Watch last nights Sky Arts Book Club Live here https://www.facebook.com/watch/?v=2783192805271517  

If you would like to support me you can by heading here https://www.patreon.com/SavidgeReads

Books Mentioned…

Trio by William Boyd
People Like Us by Hashi Mohamed
The Daylight Gate by Jeanette Winterson
Three Hours by Rosalund Lupton
My Brilliant Friend by Elena Ferrante
The Story of a New Name by Elena Ferrante
Those Who Leave and Those Who Stay by Elena Ferrante
The Story of the Lost Child by Elena Ferrante
The Lamplighters by Emma Stonex
These Women by Ivy Pochoda
This One Sky Day by Leone Ross
Kololo Hill by Neema Shah
The Correct Order of Biscuits by Adam Sharp
The River Within by Karen Powell
The Best Things by Mel Giedroyc
One August Night by Victoria Hislop
Biscuits Assorted by Jenny Robins
The Seventh Mansion by Maryse Meijer
The Secret Lives of Church Ladies by Deesha Philyaw
Pink Mountain on Locust Island by Jamie Marina Lau
From Pasta to Pigfoot by Frances Mensah Williams
Vesper Flights by Helen MacDonald
And I Do Not Forgive You by Amber Sparks
The Boy, The Mole, The Fox and the Boy by Charlie Mackesy
Home Stretch by Graham Norton
Quite by Claudia Winkleman
I Am An Island by Tamsin Calidas
Deacon King Kong by James McBride
Black Sunday by Tola Rotimi Abraham
Vera by Elizabeth Von Arnim
The Actual by Inua Williams
Hag: Forgotten Folktakes Retold
Ghosts by Dolly Alderton

Me Elsewhere...
